<br>
I would start with the BP, and get something like barbed ringmail (+11 raw AC, +40 raw HP).  <br>
<br>
Then the arms or bracers (stick with things with high raw AC, or HP).  Crystal chitin arms will give you a little more ac and 15 raw HP (i think).  Silver Chitin Wristbands (+40raw HP.)<br>
<br>
your only getting about 3hp per stamina at this point, so the stamina isnt as useful to you as raw HP, and/or AC would be.<br>
<br>
Start looking for Raw HP items, and some bigger AC<br>
<br>
if I had 45 K to work with .... this is what i would buy.<br>
<br>
2x Silver Chitin Wristbands<br>
1x Thunder Etched Gaunts, or better<br>
1x Barbed Ringmail<br>
1x Worked or better dragonskin breeches<br>
1x Crystal Chitin Armplates<br>
1x Crystal Chitin Boots (thurg MQ if you have faction)<br>
1x frostbringer<br>
<br>
then id sell the Jade Mace.<br>
<br>
heh, to think back on it, i used a similar setup as this till well into my 50s ... never had any problems. (though i used defiance instead of lammy)<br>
<br>
thats just my advice though ... feel free to play around a little with different items and of course, i dont know what your server economy is like, so i may be a little off on prices, but thats what i would aim for as far as getting rid of your crusty for a little better gear.<br>
<br>
Save buying new legs till last, and if you can afford it, pick up Blood Runed (unless you can wear cultural, then go with Fierce Heraldic, hell, if you can go cultural, skip the rest and start building your FH set up now, so you have it to equip when you hit 45)<br>
<br>
Just my 2cp ... im sure other people have different views, but this is what i would do (sorta what i did do, thanks VI for making kittys perma agnostic) <p>Master Xith N'Shezbenon<br>
